        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:44PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Columbus, or 4 miles west of Inman, moving southeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Inman, Lyman, and Lake Bowen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
